"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679115","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-01-31","<p>The General Data Protection Regulation will apply to EU member states from 25 May 2018. We expect still to be in the EU at that point, and so we will ensure that the General Data Protection Regulation will apply in the UK from then.</p><p> </p><p>As part of plans for the UK’s exit from the EU, the Government will be seeking to ensure that data flows between the UK and the EU are uninterrupted, and will be considering all the available options that will provide legal certainty for businesses and citizens alike.</p><p> </p><p>Whilst negotiations to leave the EU have not begun, it would be inappropriate to speculate in any detail as to what arrangement we will seek to put in place.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-01-31T14:47:56.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679115/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679115/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679115/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-26","UK Trade with EU: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps she is taking to secure a data adequacy decision for the UK from the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","61972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679116","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-02","<p>It will be for the Scottish Government to decide whether to seek to use European funding to support its Phase 2 broadband programme.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-02T16:38:17.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679116/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679116/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679116/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-26","Broadband: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether Phase 2 superfast broadband delivery in Scotland will receive European funding.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","61951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679117","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-02","<p>The Department does not forecast superfast broadband take-up, and does not hold information on take-up at a constituency level or on separate business and household take-up. Take-up in the broadband project covering the Rest of Scotland excluding Highlands &amp; Islands is currently just over 25%.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-02T16:35:44.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679117/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679117/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679117/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-26","Broadband: Rutherglen and Hamilton West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether her Department has made an estimate of the proportion of (a) households and (b) business premises in Rutherglen and Hamilton West constituency which are forecast to have signed up to receive superfast broadband by the end of 2017; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","61913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679118","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-31","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-01-31T16:22:47.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679118/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679118/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679118/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-26","Ministry of Defence: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much was spent on upgrading heating, washing and electrical facilities across the defence estate in each year since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","61963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679119","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-31","<p>The fault with the boiler at Wellington Barracks was identified on 23 January and fixed on 26 January. Temporary portable heaters were provided on 24 January to affected areas.</p><p>No major facilities upgrades are planned at this time. A continuous maintenance programme at Wellington Barracks ensures the site is statutory and mandatory compliant.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-01-31T16:23:27.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679119/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679119/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679119/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-26","Wellington Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the time needed (a) to repair the boiler at Wellington Barracks and (b) for wider facilities upgrades at that barracks.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","61961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679120","Department for Education","false","2017-02-01","<p>The number of citizenship teachers trained each year since academic year 2010/11 is shown in the table below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Academic Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of citizenship trainees</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>243</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>164</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>125</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>116</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>112</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>85</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>54</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><ul><li>Source: ITT Census Data Management System</li><li>The number of new entrants to Citizenship is not published in the annual ITT Census and is included as part of “Other” in the subject tables.</li></ul>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-02-01T16:30:51.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679120/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679120/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679120/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-01-26","Citizenship: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many citizenship teachers were trained in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","61973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679121","Department for Education","false","2017-02-02","<p>Allowing vetted researchers, academics and others to access extracts of this data under strictly controlled conditions helps the development and improvement of our education system for the benefit of all.</p><p>Anyone requesting data from the NPD must comply with strict confidentiality and security rules. Organisations that meet these strict criteria can apply for data. This includes media organisations.</p><p>The number of occasions an application for data from the NPD, a media organisation has been allowed in each of the years specified is detailed in the table below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of occasions NPD data has been shared with the media</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>*We have defined ‘the media’ as ‘organisations whose primary purpose is the generation of news stories for an online, print or screen/radio presence’. </em></p><p>A full list of NPD data requests that have been approved / rejected / not pursued from April 2012 to June 2016 is available on gov.uk in the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-pupil-database-requests-received" target="_blank">Third Party Published List</a>. An updated version of the ‘Third Party Published List’ showing all requests that have been approved / rejected / not pursued up to December 2016 will be available in March 2017.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-02-02T16:41:40.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679121/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679121/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679121/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-01-26","Pupils: Personal Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 10 January 2017 to Question 56640, on how many occasions National Pupil Database data has been shared with the media in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","61932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679122","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-02","<p>The UK is concerned about any actions in the South China Sea which might raise tensions or pose a risk to freedom of navigation and regional stability. As the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Boris Johnson), made clear in a speech on 18 January, we oppose the militarisation of the South China Sea.</p><p>The Foreign Secretary raised the South China Sea with Chinese State Councillor Yang Jiechi during the UK-China Strategic Dialogue in London on 20 December. He noted the importance of abiding by international law in the South China Sea and refraining from activities which could raise tensions.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-02-02T16:07:26.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679122/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679122/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679122/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-26","South China Sea: Disputed Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the level of military presence on the Paracel Islands in the South China Sea; and what recent representations he has made to his Chinese counterpart of the security situation on those islands.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","61879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679123","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-01","<p>I refer my Hon. Friend to my answer of 26 January 2017 (written PQ 60521).</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-02-01T15:39:34.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679123/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679123/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679123/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-26","Israeli Settlements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 16 January 2017 to Question 58877 and the Answer of 26 January 2017 to Question 60521, which Ministers were made aware of the text of the UN Security Council Resolution 2334 (2016) before the vote on that resolution took place.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","61906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679124","Department of Health","false","2017-02-03","<p>NHS England publishes monthly data on the number of elective and non-elective inpatient admissions to National Health Service hospital trusts, most recently for November 2016. Data are not collected for individual hospital sites within NHS trusts. The following table shows how many patients were admitted to general and acute specialties at Calderdale and Huddersfield NHS Foundation Trust in each month between June 2016 and November 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Number of patients admitted to general and acute specialties at Calderdale and Huddersfield NHS Foundation Trust, June 2016 to November 2016</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Month in 2016</p></td><td><p>Elective admissions</p></td><td><p>Non-elective admissions</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June</p></td><td><p>5,291</p></td><td><p>3,653</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July</p></td><td><p>5,159</p></td><td><p>3,624</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August</p></td><td><p>5,490</p></td><td><p>3,332</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September</p></td><td><p>5,395</p></td><td><p>3,681</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October</p></td><td><p>5,280</p></td><td><p>4,033</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November</p></td><td><p>5,610</p></td><td><p>3,711</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Source</em>: NHS England, monthly activity return:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/hospital-activity/monthly-hospital-activity/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/hospital-activity/monthly-hospital-activity/</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-02-03T11:59:52.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679124/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679124/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679124/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-26","Huddersfield Royal Infirmary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients have been admitted to Huddersfield Royal Infirmary in each of the last six months.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","61921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679125","Department of Health","false","2017-01-31","<p>As with all borderline substances, any application for a gluten-free food product to be included in Part XV of the Drug Tariff must include a statement of the total price of the product to the National Health Service. Applicants must confirm that the total price of the product is inclusive of all distribution costs and indicate where they see their product being positioned within the current list of Advisory Committee on Borderline Substances (ACBS)-approved products. As part of its overall consideration, the Committee will benchmark the proposed price submitted by the applicant against similar products already included within Part XV.</p><p> </p><p>The ACBS will only consider gluten-free food products based on white, brown or wholemeal grains that are considered to be “dietary staples”, including:</p><p> </p><p>- plain breakfast cereals containing no added sugar;</p><p>- breads and rolls;</p><p>- crackers and crispbreads;</p><p>- flours and bread mixes;</p><p>- Pastas;</p><p>- pizza bases; and</p><p>- xanthan gum.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","61965","2017-01-31T17:28:47.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679125/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679125/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/679125/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-26","Coeliac Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what criteria are used to determine the price of gluten-free products accepted by the Advisory Committee on Borderline Substances recommended list which forms Part XV of the Drug Tariff.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","61964"
